<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 21 at 7:44AM CDT  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...Areas of Fog Affecting the Lower Texas Coastline...
Surface observations and satellite data indicate that areas of
fog have developed along the lower Texas coastline early this
morning. Some areas of locally dense fog are reducing visibilities
of around 1/4 of a mile, mainly on South Padre Island and Port
Isabel in addition to the Causeway.
These areas of fog should improve steadily throughout the morning
hours allowing the visibilities to increase.
Early morning motorists in South Padre Island and Port Isabel
are urged to reduce speed, use low beam headlights, and avoid
following other vehicles too closely in the areas of denser fog
through the morning hours.</description>
